Name of the program: TinyInvaders(AB3)
This is my poor idea of a SPACE INVADERS clone for all the Classic
AMIGAs.
It is not completed but the game bones are present so take it as
it is.
This is the fifteenth upload and the version is not changed seen I
have made few improvements.
The bullet fires now are with sound, finally!
At the end of the game there is a musical present, good listening!
Now if you are bored to wait for the text messages press a key to
show all them.
If the cannon bullet hits the ufo, the player gains fifty points
and the number is showed as for the others invader hits.
Now each move of the invaders has a sound just to give a bit more
of suspence.
Now there is a sound for the cannon, the invader and the ufo hits
also!
Now if you press the Z key at start the game area is sides doubled
for a better view on an interlaced Workbench; I suggest you to try
this game mode but not to use it on a standard NTSC or PAL
Workbench!
Now all the messages in the enlarged mode are double sided too!
The colours matching is better, on a two colours Workbench also,
and now the background stripes colour is no more random, it is
sequential!
There was a problem of program lock after the first level; now I
should have solved it.
I have removed some source code errors, some bugs and improved
some other things, enjoy!
Now the number of the points for the hitted invader if fine, it
moves with the other invaders and now two numbers can appear
together.
Now there is a shape for the hitted cannon.
Now if there are some black colours into your Workbench palette
they are skipped from the game backdrop fading count.
Now for each level before can be added an invaders column and then
can be added an invaders row, all this is no more totally random.
Now at end there is a black squares fading effect.
Now there is a background music.
Now there are the defences!
Now there are the big stars at the top!
Now you can play on a four (4) colour Workbench!
Now the source code has been optimized under AmiBlitz3 3.1.0.
If you know how to improve it please let me know, I will
appreciate it.
